# Frontend rules

## Project layout

```
frontend/
  app/
    layout.tsx
    page.tsx               # redirects to /trips/trip_lisbon for the demo
    trips/[id]/page.tsx    # main 3-column screen
    api/                   # Next.js API routes (proxy to FastAPI backend)
  components/
    chat-panel.tsx
    trip-workspace.tsx
    todo-card.tsx
    booking-pane.tsx
    booking-card.tsx
    voice-button.tsx       # Phase 2
  lib/
    api.ts                 # typed fetch wrappers
    types.ts               # mirrors backend Pydantic models
    polling.ts             # poll-every-2s hook
  styles/globals.css
  package.json
```

## Stack rules

- **Next.js 15 App Router.** Server components by default. `"use client"` only for hooks/browser APIs.
- **Tailwind + shadcn/ui.** No Material, no Chakra, no other UI lib.
- **TypeScript strict mode.** No `any`. Reach for `unknown` or define real types.
- **`fetch` + React Query (`@tanstack/react-query`).** `refetchInterval` for polling.
- **Polling, not websockets.** UI polls `/trips/:id/todos` every 2s. Phase 1 doesn't justify SSE.

## Layout: 3 columns on desktop

≥ 1024px:

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Header: trip name + user name (top right)                │
├────────────┬───────────────────────┬──────────────────────┤
│ Chat       │ Trip workspace        │ Booking pane         │
│ (~30%)     │ (~40%)                │ (~30%)               │
│            │                       │                      │
│ messages   │ todo list             │ pending booking      │
│ + input    │ + trip cards          │ cards w/ "Open" btn  │
└────────────┴───────────────────────┴──────────────────────┘
```

Below 1024px: tabs at the bottom (Chat / Trip / Bookings). Default Chat.

## Component patterns

- Functional, named exports. No default exports except Next.js page/layout files.
- Files cap at ~150 lines. Split if longer.
- State: `useState` local, React Query for server state. No Redux/Zustand.
- No prop drilling beyond 2 levels.

## Polling hook

```ts
// lib/polling.ts
import { useQuery } from "@tanstack/react-query";

export function useTodos(tripId: string) {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ["todos", tripId],
    queryFn: () => fetchTodos(tripId),
    refetchInterval: 2000,
    refetchIntervalInBackground: false,
  });
}
```

Same shape for `useTrip(tripId)` (5s interval is fine).

## Todo card — the demo's hero element

The single most-watched UI element in the demo. Spend polish budget here.

A todo card shows:
- Status icon (animated for `running`)
- Text of the todo
- Sub-status line in muted color (e.g. "FlightAgent · Searching options...")
- For `running`: subtle pulse animation
- For `needs_user`: prominent CTA highlight
- For `done`: collapsed, checkmark
- "✨ Used: 'Alex prefers morning departures'" badge when `memory_facts_used` is non-empty
- Smooth transitions between status states

```tsx
const statusIcon = {
  pending: <Clock className="text-muted" />,
  running: <Loader2 className="animate-spin text-blue-500" />,
  needs_user: <AlertCircle className="text-amber-500" />,
  done: <Check className="text-green-500" />,
  failed: <X className="text-red-500" />,
}[todo.status];
```

## Booking pane — side-by-side browser feel

Major travel sites block iframe embedding via `X-Frame-Options`. Don't iframe Booking.com — it won't work. The "side-by-side browser" is a UX illusion:

- Right pane shows browser-chrome frame: fake URL bar with destination URL, favicon, "Open in new tab →" button.
- Click → `window.open(booking_url, "_blank", "noopener,noreferrer")`.
- After click: pane switches to "We've opened the booking page in a new tab — finish there and come back" with a big "I booked it" button.
- "I booked it" → `POST /todos/:id/confirm` → todo card moves to confirmed section.

Never `<iframe src={external_url}>` with a real travel domain. Silently broken.

## API client

```ts
// lib/api.ts
const API_BASE = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE ?? "http://localhost:8000";

export async function fetchTodos(tripId: string): Promise<Todo[]> {
  const res = await fetch(`${API_BASE}/trips/${tripId}/todos`);
  if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`Failed: ${res.status}`);
  return res.json();
}
```

Types in `lib/types.ts` mirror backend Pydantic models. Keep in sync manually.

## Styling rules

- Tailwind utility classes inline. No CSS modules.
- shadcn's `cn()` helper for conditional classes.
- Palette: neutral grays + one accent (blue or amber). No rainbow.
- Spacing: `space-y-*`, `gap-*` over manual margins.
- No custom fonts. System stack is fine.

## Loading / error / empty states

Every fetch needs three states. The demo will not look professional if a panel goes blank.

- Loading: skeleton, not spinner, when layout is known
- Error: small inline message + retry button, not a toast
- Empty: friendly placeholder ("Via will show booking links here")

## What NOT to add

- ❌ Auth / login. User hardcoded as `alex` server-side.
- ❌ Dark mode toggle. Pick light, ship.
- ❌ Heavy animations beyond simple transitions.
- ❌ shadcn components you don't need.
- ❌ Storybook, testing libs, e2e tests.
- ❌ Custom design system. Tailwind + shadcn IS the design system.
- ❌ RSC for data that polls. Polling = client component.
